passages.text:
As the end of your eleven-year betrothment approached, you found your attention diverted by a sudden threat to your mother's business interests. The expedition to the mining colony and back shouldn't have taken more than a month or so. You curse into the frigid air.
{(set: $inv to it + (a:"locket"))}
[[Blight the gods who wrote this journey into my life!|Intro9]]

You had heard tell of an order of exiles who live in the mountains to the West who have foresworn the intrusion of the written word. These apostates, barely tolerated by virtue of their remoteness, pass on the secrets of their religion by whispering in the ears of initiates in darkened rooms far above the ground. That sounded like a good place.
{
(set: $playerTags to it + (a:"spiritual"))
(set: "people" of $knowledge to it + (datamap: "Whispering Keepers","An isolated order who hold a heretical ideology - that the written word is not inviolate, and that the secret history of the world can only be truly told in whispers"))
}
[[Could I not have been offered a final journey through the land of my birth without obstruction?|Intro9]]

You would plough your field wherever the soil looked less than dead. You would pitch a tent somewhere with a view away from the land that had cast you out, and build a lodge for yourself to whatever specification you pleased. You'd cut down trees, un-notarised, and with the plants you'd grow, you'd cook whatever you wanted.
{(set: $inv to it + (a:"seed-bag"))}
[[But, there is nothing it this land that does not fail at the first step|Intro9]]

(if: $playerTags contains "boundhands")[You make an attempt to rummage through the straw, but it's too difficult with your hands tied like this. The smell of human sweat and fear that emanates from the disturbed bedding is palpable.]
(else-if: ($inv contains "bone brooch") is false)[You scrabble through the bedding, desperate for any sign of another life. A small brooch, carved from bone, drops from a dry and musty handful of straw. (set: $broochonfloor to true)]
(else:)[You dig through the straw, but now you find nothing but disappointment]

{
(if: $broochonfloor is true)[
(link: "pick up the brooch")[You pick it up(set: $broochonfloor to false)(set: $inv to it+(a:"bone brooch"))]
]}
[[sit back|Entrance2]]

A large piece of curved green glass, wickedly sharp.

(if: (history:)'s 2ndlast is "hallway 3" or (history:)'s 2ndlast is "Hallway3a" or (history:)'s 2ndlast is "Hallway3b")[(link: "peer through the glass")[(goto: "Hallway5a")]

](else:)[The light glints dimly off the shard's jagged edge.

](if: $playerTags contains "boundhands")[(link: "cut your bonds")[(set: $playerTags to it - (a:"boundhands"))(goto: (history:)'s 2ndlast)]]
(link: "Done")[(goto: (history:)'s 2ndlast)]

//if you slide down the chute from the hallway//
(set: $filth to it + 5)(set: $health to it-1)
The chute is dark, narrow, and slick with blood. Unable to manoeuvre, you feel your head crack on a jagged rock on the way down.

{(if: $health<1)[[[You fall into darkness->the body cellar transition]]]
(else:)[Suddenly, the chute disappears from underneath you and you're falling.]}

[[you land with a thud->the body cellar]]]

