(either: "You bed down on the chilly floor and look at towards the little square of light that is the window of Croach's shack. You envy him his food and his rich ale, but most of all you envy him the warmth of his fire.","You bed down in a huddle with the other members of the chain gang, careless of personal space and of the reeking smell, seeking only warmth.","You doze fitfully, having dreams of pits and shovelling that you can scarce distinguish from your daily travails. A plague on this accursed place.", "Another day comes to its desolate end with you searching for a patch of ground to sleep on devoid of water, filth, or other sleepers.")

